column1: full on off, and swinging away from Babar. He chooses to shoulder his arms
length ball on off, and turning into him. Carved off the back foot to cover
fuller on the stumps. Defended off the front foot with soft hands. Four fielders run in to stop the single. Sharp from the Quetta fielders!
full on leg, and meeting the batsman near middle stump. Pushed to mid-off for a quick single, and they complete it despite the fielder's attempt at a direct hit
full just outside off, and coming inwards. Splices a straight drive to mid-on for a quick single
full on off, and he prods forward to drive. Check-shot to mid off. A tidy over from Tanvir to kick things off
length ball on off, and sliding inwards. Defended off the back foot towards the off side
length ball on off, and he punches off the back foot to the bowler
length ball on middle, and skidding in. Flicked off the back foot to mid-on
full on off, and he flicks off his pads to the vacant midwicket region for a single
length ball, wide outside off, but turning into Munro. Backs away to cut, but can't beat point
there's the first boundary! Full just outside off, but Munro reaches towards the ball, opens his levers, and slaps a flat-batted shot over Nawaz's head. Ruins the bowler's otherwise brilliant over
full on middle, and flicked through to deep midwicket! Fielder on the leg side has absolutely no chance
full outside leg, and skidding through to the keeper. Babar misses the flick
full on leg, and the attempted flick towards the on-side doesn't hit his bat. Ball hits his knee-roll, and rolls away. Tanvir's appeal is turned down because the ball pitched outside leg
length ball on leg, and he nonchalantly flicks fine past the keeper's left! Guides it to fine leg for four
length ball on off, and cut square from near his body. Misfield from cover point allows the dot ball to go for two
full on off, and caressed through the covers! Firm press forward, and then his bat's speed does the rest
was that dropped? Full on off, and he tries to defend. But the ball moves in, and perhaps grazes the inside-half of his bat, before going to Sarfraz's left. He fluffs the difficult take though
slower ball, low full toss on off. Tapped to cover for a quick single
slower ball, full just outside off, and flicked with the bats closed face to deep midwicket
low full toss on off, and tapped to long-on
yorker on off, and he digs this away to cover. They scamper across for one, but Bravo things it's pad first and not bat. Quetta review but replays suggest it was bat first. Poor, poor decision!
low full toss on off, and muscled away to extra cover
slower ball again. Dipping yorker just outside off, and worked off his toes to midwicket
length ball on leg, and going further down. Babar misses the flick, and given wide
length ball, just wide outside off, and punched with the bat's open face to deep extra cover
back of a length on middle, and once again drifting down the leg side. Babar misses the flick, but Karachi collect the extra run
back of a length, just outside off, and he muscles a pull over the fielder at mid-on! Races away for four

full on off, and driven to mid-on for a quick run. Munro is asked to return to his crease very late, and he stretches towards the crease to get in. But there's a direct hit from mid-on, and the umpires want to go upstairs, but Munro is safe
length ball on middle, and steered with the bat's open face to the keeper's right
length ball outside off, and Munro shapes up to hammer a cut through the off side. Beaten by some extra pace!
back of a length on off, and the ball is soaring over the batsman's head! Another extra
length ball on leg, and he tries to flick towards square leg. Grazes his thigh guard and rolls away to square leg
length ball on leg, and nudged off his pads to the leg side
slower ball, overpitched outside off, and he drills a square drive through the point region!
overpitched on middle, and he digs a straight drive down to mid-on. Enough time to scamper across for one
full on leg stump, and he muscles a flat-batted swipe to mid-off
guided beautifully past third man! Yorker, just outside off, but Munro offers the horizontal bat and guides this behind square on the off side!
full, outside leg stump, and whipped off his boots to short fine leg. Fawad dives to his right and intercepts
full on middle, and Munro can't get under this. Driven back to the bowler
full on leg, and the wrong'un goes across the batsman. Edged to short third man
length ball on off, and skidding into the right hander. He makes some room, and taps this inside-out to mid off
length ball, outside leg stump, and Munro wants to work this towards the leg side. Misses, and the ball hits his knee roll
full on middle, and turning away. Driven down the ground to long on.
full on off, and turning away from Babar. Pushed off the front foot to cover. A tidy start to Fawah's spell
half-tracker on off, and the slider is pulled down to long on. Just a single
length ball, from around the wicket, and Babar comes down the wicket, before nudging it away to square leg for one
that's a biggie! Full on leg, and he goes down on one knee, before slog-sweeping over the leg-side fence!
flatter, and wider outside off. Cut away furiously to the fielder at deep point
full on middle, and Babar skips down the ground, before driving to wide long on
short and wide outside off, and he slaps a cut to deep point once more. They walk across for one
full on off, and he slog-sweeps to deep midwicket. Protection there though
full just outside off, and driven away to cover. Can't pinch the single though
length ball on leg, and flicked off his pads to wide long on. Protection there too
full just outside off, and driven to cover
length ball, wide outside off, and he rocks back to cut square. Sweeper-fielder cleans up

big appeal for Sarfaraz for caught behind, and the umpire raises his finger! Viv RIchards is excited. Full on middle, and the googly turns further away from Munro. He goes for a big slog-sweep, but the ball takes his top-edge, and Sarfaraz takes a sharp catch. There's the first wicket
length ball on off, but skidding into his body from around the wicket. Babar makes room, and punches to mid-off
flatter on off, and he walks down the wicket, before punching to long off
full on leg, and clipped off his toes to the fielder lurking at short midwicket
length ball on off, and he steers a punched shot to wide long off
length ball, just outside off, and Babar steps out again. Tries to punch towards long-off, but instead under-edges the shot into the pitch
another length ball skidding in, and he muscles a swiped-shot to long on for one. Keeps the strike
length ball on middle, and spinning across his pads. Flicked away to short fine leg
length ball on middle, and straightening after pitching. Nudged off his hips to deep midwicket
full on leg, and he goes for a big one. Gets down on one knee, and slog sweeps over cow corner!
full just outside off, and he check-drives to deep extra cover. They walk across for one
full just outside off, and driven away from his body to wide long off
length ball on off, and the googly spins inwards. Clipped off his pads to square leg
full on middle, and he looks to deposit this over midwicket. Goes for an expansive slog sweep, but the ball hits his body and nearly takes leg stump

Umar Akmal holds on! Nawaz sees Livingstone coming down the wicket, and therefore bowls wide outside off. Tries to flat-bat a shot over Nawaz, but toe ends it instead. Long off and long on converge to take the catch, but Umar calls for the catch, and completes it without running into his team-mate
length ball on off, and nudged off his pads to the leg side
full on off, and he clips this away to the leg side with soft hands
up and over! Full on off, but he manages to get his bat-swing under the ball. Picks this up, and deposits it over long on
back of a length, faster outside off, and Ingram rocks back to pull over deep midwicket. Twelve runs to end the over as Nawaz finishes his spell with 1 for 35
full on off, and flicked with the bat's closed face to square leg
length ball, from around the wicket, and Ingram rides the bounce to play a firm punch. Stopped at cover point
length ball, from around the wicket again. Ball's angling into the keeper, and cut to point
length ball, wide outside off, and he tries to cut. But beaten for pace as Sarfaraz pouches it low
length ball, wide outside off, and that's been hammered off the back foot! Flies past point as Babar moves on to 46
waist-high full toss on middle, and steered off his pads to deep midwicket
slower through the air, full just outside off, and he clatters a straight shot to long-on's right
full outside off, and Ingram picks this up beautifully. Sees the googly go away from him, and adjusts late to muscle an inside-out shot over long off! The players in the Karachi dugout run for over
full on off, and guided off the front foot to cover point
length ball on leg stump. Spinning across the batsman, and cut square to deep point
length ball on off, and worked away with the bat's closed face to wide long on
slapped! Length ball on middle, but Ingram backs away to cut. Played in front of square, and races away to the extra-cover fence. What an innings he's playing. Fawad's spell ends at 1-32.
fifty for Babar! Length ball on off, and tapped away to cover for a quick run. A sedate celebration

slower ball, full from around the wicket on off, and Ingram's beaten by the lack of pace. Through his leg-side flick too early, and the ball hits his front leg. Easiest of lbw decisions for the umpire. Karachi review the decision, but there's no edge, and the ball seems to be hitting off stump. Ball tracking concurs too. Ingram falls after a 10-ball 24
wild full toss on middle, and flicked off his pads to square leg. Gets off the mark
full and wide outside off, and he throws his hands at this. Under-edges the shot past the keeper's right, and collects a lucky boundary

length ball on middle, and tapped off the back foot to the vacant midwicket region. Nobody there, so the bowler needs to run across the ground. Enough time to scamper back for the second. Smart batting
full and wide outside off, and he tries to go for a drive through mid-off. Ball deviates slightly, and it's taken his outside edge. Hasnain strikes again!
back of a length, just outside leg stump, and worked off his hips to square leg. Slower ball to start the spell
shottt! back of a length, wide outside off, and he tiptoes to cut this right over point! Karachi need a few more of those
back to the slower ball. Full and wide outside off, and driven away to deep extra cover for a single
slower ball, full toss low on middle, and nudged off his pads to square leg

full, just outside off, and he tries to drive straight. The ball pops in the air, and Bravo takes a catch on his followthrough. Bravo believes that the ball has hit the boot and come to him directly, but the batsman thinks he's wedged the shot into the ground before it hit the boot. The umpires have a chat, and the TV umpire says 'ground first'. Iftikhar survives
full on off, and driven to long on for a single
back of a length on off, and he swivels to pull along the ground. Protection at deep midwicket though

length ball on middle, and this has been muscled off the back foot! Pulled to cow corner, and it hits the base of the foam that forms the boundary-rope. Just wide of the fielder at deep midwicket. Is that a four or a six? The TV umpire says...four!
full on off, and a bit of swing away from Dunk. He clears his front leg, and lifts this beautiful straight drive over Tanvir's head!
back of a length on off, and pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
full outside leg, and steered behind square to short fine leg
full toss on leg stump, from around the wicket. Clipped to midwicket for just a single. Dunk keeps strike
low full toss on off, and drilled to long off
full just outside off, and Iftikhar gets deep in his crease, before muscling a straight slog past the umpire! Long-on a spectator near the boundary
length ball, wide outside off, and he drags a slog towards long on. Drops just short of the fielder there
yorker, on leg stump, and worked off his toes to deep backward square. Man riding the boundary intercepts
yorker on off, and dug away to the leg side. They scamper across for one
another yorker on middle, and all Dunk can do is splice a drive to deep extra cover. Finishes his spell for 0-34
full on leg, but he doesn't pick the slower ball. Goes for a slog towards the leg side, but heaves it into the air. Deep midwicket calls for the catch, and runs forward to complete it

thumped over long off! What a shot. Full on off, but he uses his bottom hand to lift this right over Umar at long off. Umar tried to take a catch from over his head, but the ball went through his hands
yorker on middle, and he muscles a drive to wide long on. Misfield from the Rossouw allows Iftikhar to get back on strike

back of a length outside off, but angling into the right hander. He backs away to make some room, but his cut-shot has gone finer than expected! Short third-man can't cut it off, and that's a useful boundary for Karachi
full on off, and he goes down on one knee to slog. Slightly deceived by the pace, and therefore he top-edges the shot over short fine leg! What are these bats!
full just outside off, and he splices an on-drive to long on. Keeps the strike
yorker on middle, and he manages to clip this through to deep midwicket! Excellent from the batsman, and even better running from the duo. They scamper back for the second

Shahzad can't believe it! Full on off, and the straight drive goes to Shahzad at long off. Easy pick up for the outfielder, but he makes a big mess of it. Ball hits his thumb, and rolls away to the boundary. He buries his head inside his palm
full toss angling into his body, and flicked fine off his pads! Fielder is too square, and that's four more
overpitched on off, and he drills a drive down to long off. Shahzad does better this time
low full toss just outside off, and he splices a drive to deep extra cover
yorker on leg, and he clips this fine to fine leg. Rossouw dives near the boundary, and stops the four. Karachi finish on 190!
full just outside off, and he mistimes a drive to mid off
length ball, just outside off, and carved off the back foot to cover
full outside off, and turning away from the right hander. Driven to cover
full on leg, and clipped to midwicket. They want a single, but the midwicket fielder doesn't allow that to happen
full just outside off, and defended with soft hands to cover. They scamper across for one
full on off, and the leg-side clip takes an inside-edge onto his pads. Ball rolls away to cover for a single
full outside off, and he caresses a cover drive through the infield! What a glorious shot
oye, hoye, hoye! full on off, and this time he prods forward to drive square through point! Third man can't cut it off either
full outside off, and that's a hat-trick of fours! Takes a tiny step towards the line of the ball, and drills a cover drive for another boundary. What a start for Shehzad
length ball on off, and he punches off the back foot to cover
length ball on middle, and steered to third man for a single
full and wide outside off, and he brings the bat down to drive to deep point
length ball on off, but swinging inwards. Bat-padded towards the off side and they run across for a single. Bowler thinks Watson's lbw, but replays show it's all bat
full on leg, and he attempts a fine flick. Ball hits his pad, and rolls past the keeper's left. But Dunk dives to intercept, and saves atleast a single
length ball angling in, and nudged off his pads to square leg
length ball on middle, but going down the leg side
full on middle, but once again going down the leg side with the angle. Did that graze his pad? Naw
length ball, wide outside off, and he rides the bounce to punch to cover. Intercepted
length ball, wide outside off, and he drags a leg-side slog to midwicket. No real timing behind that shot
length ball on middle, and flicked to deep midwicket. Sharp work in the deep, with the fielder parrying the ball back. Saves the boundary
length ball on off, and flicked off his hips to midwicket. Jog across for a single
length ball angling into leg, and he swivels to pull along the ground. Mistimed to deep backward square
flicked over deep backward square! Full on leg stump, and he uses his wrists to deposit a lifted shot over the leg-side boundary. Magnifique
length ball just outside off, and punched off the back foot through point! Ball racing away for another boundary
full on middle, and he drives with the bat's open face to mid off
length ball on middle, and he displays some fast hands to pull to deep midwicket
full just outside off, and he drives after skipping down the ground. Smacked to mid-off
inside edged! Watson very lucky. Slider on middle, and he tries to pull. Ball stays low, takes the under-edge and squeaks past the keeper for a boundary
length ball on leg, and Watson backs away to punch straight. Misses the shot, and the ball hits his pads, but the delivery is going down leg
length ball, just outside off, and punched to long-on's right!
full just outside off, and tapped away to cover for a quick single
length ball on leg, and cramping Watson for space. Misses the pull as the ball hits his body
full and wide outside off stump, and he slaps a square drive through to the point boundary!
length ball on off, and pulled along the ground to deep midwicket. Dangerous second run, but it needed a direct hit from the deep. Watson too slow while taking the second
length ball on leg, and flicked off his pads to square leg
biggie! Length ball, just outside off, and Watson levers a straight drive over the bowler's head!
length ball, just outside off, and he opens the bat's face to run a shot fine down to third man!
length ball on off, and worked off his pads to deep midwicket
length ball on off, and punched off the back foot to wide long on
back of a length, just outside off, and worked from outside the stumps to long on
full on middle, and Watson leans forward, before swing across the line to the leg side. Toe-ends the shot, and it's been taken at deep midwicket! The Karachi crowd rejoices!
length ball just outside off, and punched to short cover
length ball, just outside off, and he flat-bats a shot back to the bowler
length ball on off, and punched to long on. They walk across for one
full on middle, and sliding into leg stump. Flicked to square leg
full outside off, and driven away from his body to deep extra cover
full outside off, and he splices a cover drive to the infielder. Slight fumble from Iftikhar allows the batsmen to take the single
length ball, just outside off, and defended towards cover
drilled to long on, but excellent from Ingram there to stop the four. Full on middle, and this was hammered down the ground
yorker on middle, and worked off his toes to deep midwicket
length ball on middle, and angling down leg. Tries to whip it away off his pads, but misses. Ball grazed his thigh-pad there
full on middle, and he skips down the ground to lift a shot over long-on. Ball goes through the gap between bat and body, but the keeper can't hold on. Missed stumping opportunity
length ball on off, and worked off his pads to deep midwicket
full on off, and he stays on the back foot, and opens his stance. Swings across the line, and deposits a six over deep midwicket!

beautiful from the bowler! A full 100 marks to the young man for his streetsmart skills. Expected Rossouw to give him the charge, so bowled fast outside off stump. Rossouw misses the cut because of the delivery's pace, and the keeper whips the bails off. Excellent from Umer
length ball, just outside off, and defended away
length ball on off, and pushed off the back foot to deep midwicket
back of a length on off, and punched back to the bowler
length ball, wide outside off, and through to the keeper
slider on off, and carved off the back foot to deep extra cover
length ball, just wide outside off, and tapped to cover
fuller, just outside off, and pushed to mid off
full and wide outside off, and Shahzad's expansive cover drive falls short of the fielder
length ball outside off, and turning further away. Cut off the back foot to point
length ball, wide outside off, and he rocks back to pull a shot over deep midwicket! Timing!
length ball, just outside off, and he looks to cut. Spliced to point
length ball, wide outside off, and he slaps a cut to point
full and wide outside off, and he hammers a drive to deep extra cover for a single
length ball on middle, and flicked away to deep midwicket
full on off, and he swings across the line. Inside-edged to the fielder at deep backward square
full, in the slot on off, and Akmal plants his front leg across the stumps, before hammering a slog over deep midwicket. What a way to get Quetta's 100!
slower ball, full on middle, and clobbered to mid-off for one
full toss, wide outside off, and slapped past point to the man in the deep
Fifty for Shahzad! Gets there with a six. Length ball angling into his hips, and he whips a shot off his waist. Soars over deep backward square. A very sedate celebration, acknowledging the applause
full on off, and driven to mid off. They scamper across for one
yorker on middle, and worked away to midwicket. Just a single
full on middle, and flicked square to deep midwicket. Just a single
full and straight again, and he works this off his toes behind square. Intercepted by square leg
low full toss o middle, and he slogs towards the leg side. Mistimed to deep midwicket
yorker on leg, and nudged off his toes to deep backward square
full on off, and he swipes a shot down to deep backward square
slogged to the right of long on. They walk across for one
hammered over deep midwicket Full on his toes, and he manages to get under this delivery. Uses his bottom hand to get the elevation, and the shot has the distance as well
back of a length on middle, and he shapes up to pull. Top-edged to deep midwicket, but dropped by Munro at the boundary. Oh dear
full on off, and he drills a straight drive to long on for a single
length ball on off, and he mistimes a leg-side pull. Ball rolls down to long on. Acrobatic effort from the fielder stops the boundary
full just outside off, and slapped to extra cover for a single
full, wide outside off, and the keeper can't hold on either
full and wide outside off, and he tries to go for an expansive drive. Sliced to the fielder in the deep, and Akmal holes out at a crucial stage!
length ball on off, and pulled along the ground to deep midwicket. Ingram tries to cut it off with a diving effort, but the ball bursts through his hand. Useful four
full just outside off, and defended towards the off side. Umer runs to his left to stop the ball
length ball on middle, and he skips down the ground, to tap a shot to long on
flatter, angling in, and carved off the back foot to cover. Well stopped by the infielder
length ball on middle, and the attempted back-foot punch takes an edge to point. What an excellent spell from Umer!
length ball on off, and he slogs towards the leg side. Mistimed to cow corner
back of a length on middle, and he shapes up to pull. Ball slides down the leg side, and the umpire spreads his arms wide
back of a length, wide outside off, and punched square to point. Can't find the gap though!
low full toss on leg, and flicked away to the deep backward-square fielder
full and wide outside off, and he tries to drive through extra cover. Ball comes off the inside-half of the bat, and straight to the bowler
back of a length, just outside off, and Bravo's been deceived by the slower ball. Through to the keeper
full and straight, and he drives inside-out to wide long off. Keeps the strike, not sure Quetta want that though
yorker on leg, and that's inside-edged onto his body. They scamper across for one
full and wide outside leg, and he lets it go through
hammered! Full on leg, and he opens his stance before depositing a lofted shot over deep midwicket!
what a blinder from Shehzad! Another one. Full toss on leg, and he swivels across to the leg side for a huge six. Shehzad wants the no-ball for height, but the square-leg umpire disagrees
length ball just outside off, and he drags a front-foot loft over to long on
yorker on leg, and clipped off his boots to deep backward square
third six of the over! My oh my oh my! Pace on the bat, full on leg stump, and he slogs towards deep midwicket to get the tournament's 301st six!
full and wide outside off, and left alone
low full toss, but wide outside off, and Bravo clatters a drive over cover to the off-side boundary. Quetta need 24 off 17
back of a length on off, and he ducks under this ball. Nice comeback
back of a length, just outside off, and he skips down the ground to clear the off side. Ball goes past his bat
slower ball, full just outside off, and Bravo fails to connect. Ball rolls into the keeper's gloves
make that four! Full and wide outside off, but Bravo can't hit the shot over extra cover. Ball goes past his outside edge, and it's also inside the tramlines
yorker on leg, and flicked to short fine leg. Bravo keeps strike
length ball on middle, and he misses the leg-side flick. Ball hits his thigh and Shehzad calls for the run
full, wide outside off, and Shehzad can't connect with the drive. But no harm, it's been called a wide
into the 90s! Full toss, juicy on his hips, and clattered over the leg-side boundary

full on off, and he goes towards the off side, before lifting a shot to deep midwicket. Shehzad wants the seocnd run, and Ingram's flat throw goes straight to the bowler. Yamin swiftly whips the bails off, and Bravo is short! That means it's only one run, but Shehzad is back on strike. Not a terrible result for Quetta
full and wide outside off, and he crunches a drive down to deep point
length ball, wide outside off, and he goes for a cut. Misses the shot, and that's been given a wide! Yamin unlucky here
full, and wide outside off again, and Anwar doesn't shuffle across. Goes beyond the tramlines, so Quetta earn another run
full just outside off, and slapped to extra cover. Quick single as Imad misses the direct hit from the deep
another wide. Full outside off, and he goes for a straight drive. Once again, touch-and-go, but the umpire has the final word
low full toss, wide outside off, and Shehzad has slapped a shot over point for four! Moves on to 99
full and wide outside off, and he carves a shot over point. Falls just short of the boundary, and is intercepted by the fielder

length ball, just outside off, and he flat-bats a shot to mid off. But Ingram dives across his right, and takes an absolute stunner! Shehzad falls for 99! Heartbreak but he gets a hug from sir Viv in the dugout
length ball, wide outside off, and the attempted cut has been edged to the keeper! Two wickets in two balls, and Anwar Ali is out as well! Twist in the tail?!
back of a length on off, and pulled one-bounce to deep backward square
Shinwari takes a third! Length ball on off, ad he under-edges the ball right into his stumps. Usman Shinwari, villain in his last over, hero in the next. Quetta need 3 off the final ball for a win

Karachi win by one run and Lahore Qalandars are knocked out! Unbelievable finish to the game. Yorker on middle, and that's been inside-edged onto his pads. They can take only one run, and Usman Shinwari has completed Karachi's heist.
